Egypt â€™s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30)  rose
for a fifth day, gaining 0.8 percent to 4,249.26 at the 2:30
p.m. close in Cairo, the highest in three weeks.  The following shares rose or fell. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Arab Cotton Ginning (ACGC)   climbed 1.7 percent to 2.99
Egyptian pounds, the highest since Oct. 4. The Cairo-based
textiles manufacturer said it will pay a 20-piaster dividend on
Nov. 2 for shareholders as of Oct. 30.  Arab Polvara Spinning & Weaving Co. (APSW EY) advanced 2.2
percent to 1.88 pounds, the highest in more than two weeks. The
Egyptian textile company said worker strikes have cost the
company 3 million pounds ($503,000).  Medinet Nasr Housing (MNHD)   advanced to the highest in
three weeks, gaining 1.7 percent to 12.48 pounds. The Egyptian
real-estate developer completed design plans to turn a 5.5
million square-meter (52.9 million square-foot) land plot on the
outskirts of Cairo into a residential community, Al Mal
newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
